INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (315, 1, '2010-09-16 16:45:00', '2010-09-16 16:45:00', 'This had to have been one of the weddings we were most excited about this summer. It had been booked in our diary for over a year and we were anticipating great things! We were far from disappointed! Nick and Ruth got married in an outdoor wedding ceremony at the very quaint and lovely <a href="http://www.friarscourt.com/">Friars Court</a> in Oxfordshire. Nick and Ruth are both teachers and met at the school that they both teach at in Cowley, Oxford. As teachers their planning was exceptional and the wedding went like clock-work, even down to the weather. We have known Ruth for about 5 years, so this made this day even more special. Ruth got ready in the wedding suite at Friars Court, while Nick, in true groom fashion had settled his last minute nerves with a swift pint at the pub down the road. Ruth''s dress was very eye-catching with its royal blue sash and beaded detailed waistband. It fitted her like a dream and she looked so amazing it brought a tear or two to my eye. Friars Court totally suited the feel of the day with its quaint bridge and orchard, which was decorated with lanterns and hearts. We would certainly recommend this venue. It boasts style and professionalism.<br>After an emotional, yet really lovely and relaxed ceremony all the guests enjoyed the grounds of the court and had a game of croquet, before making their way over to the stunning barn reception. The decor was immaculate with butterfly, heart and orchid details adorning the building.<br>We had the true pleasure of being able to sneak the happy couple away for their own photos and we were delighted that the corn field was at its peak. We had noticed it when we had done our recce and we were fingers-crossed all the way that the corn would still be there. There was really so much goodness and fun at this wedding and it really was a joy and pleasure to witness two lovely people tie the knot, but also to capture their perfectly planned day. All day Nick and Ruth were commenting on how well it went and we couldn''t have imagined it to have been any more perfect. Thank you both for letting us enjoy your day. You are such a great pair! x<br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4144/4995820989_721c14876e.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4144/4995820989_721c14876e.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4144/4995821449_95f7c8513a.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4144/4995821449_95f7c8513a.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4090/4996428676_fb38c54179.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4090/4996428676_fb38c54179.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4085/4995822125_d7d52f5597.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4085/4995822125_d7d52f5597.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4154/4996428924_555612e5a9.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4154/4996428924_555612e5a9.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4133/4995955055_4cfa99dc9e.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4133/4995955055_4cfa99dc9e.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4085/4995821653_6b2006d4e9.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4085/4995821653_6b2006d4e9.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4104/4996428188_2a8787252a.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4104/4996428188_2a8787252a.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4108/4995822803_f63986d919.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4108/4995822803_f63986d919.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4105/4996429398_a864dab058.jpg"><img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4105/4996429398_a864dab058.jpg" alt="" border="0"></a><br><br><a href="