INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (142, 1, '2012-07-11 09:00:00', '2012-07-11 09:00:00', '<div>So, as Im putting this blogpost together I can actually hear the accetns and laugh of Sian the bride! Love it! Now, these guys, Ollie (also know as Charlie) and Sian are super great. It might be because they are yet another  Brummie/Welsh combination, or could just be because they are great! We do have a little thing about Brummie/Welsh combos! :P</div>\n<div>Sian and Ollie were married at the beautiful Manobier Castle (the castle where the BBCs The Lion, The Witch and The Wardbrobe was filmed!) They had their reception at the Castle Mead hotel, literally a stones throw away from the castle, so it was all very relaxed and easy for all of us involved in their day. From start to finish, we laughed. Sian was so happy and giggly with her pals while she got ready, I could have spent the whole day just photographing her smiling. </div>\n<div>When Sian and her bridal party entered Manobier Castle there was an amazing male voice choir singing, as only the welsh know how, in tight, close harmonies. It was magical. She almost floated down the aisle to the beautiful melody. There her ''andsome prince was there to meet her!</div>\n<div>The rest they say is history. We pootled on down to the beach, again a stones throw from the castle and allowed these guys time to be together, well, nearly, apart from us and our cameras and a few visiting beach goers! Had fun, although, it was pretty nippy!</div>\n<div>Then back to the marquee for their wedding feast and a pretty cool "icecream" cake and some proper fun grooving and moving!</div>\n<div>Thank you so much Ollie and Sian for allowing us to share in your day. x x o&c</div>\n<div> </div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-o7MXIxihqbM/T_x6Y-MrbmI/AAAAAAAAAvI/FN-Da-n_94s/s1600/LIB+blog_044.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-o7MXIxihqbM/T_x6Y-MrbmI/AAAAAAAAAvI/FN-Da-n_94s/s1600/LIB+blog_044.jpg"></a>