INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (145, 1, '2012-05-29 14:45:00', '2012-05-29 14:45:00', '<div></div>\n<div>\n<span></span>Since having our beautiful little daughter our blogging has been left slightly by the way side and although this has taken me most of the day to put together between feeds, sleeps and nappy changes here, finally, is another of our wonderful weddings from 2011. We are busy, busy capturing wedding this year and will have some sneak peaks up shortly. We promise! We''re having a lot of fun!</div>\n<div>Hugo and Charlotte were married in the beautiful Cotswolds village Bibury. Imagine the scene, Cotswolds stone house, lush green surroundings... yep, pretty idyllic!</div>\n<div>Charlotte is such a beautifully happy, smiley stunner and Hugo, well, we think he looks like Christian Bale! (what do you think!)</div>\n<div>With a beautiful French vintage dress Charlotte married Hugo in large church, then celebrating in style at the amazing <a href="http://www.nationaltrust.org.uk/lodge-park-and-sherborne-estate/">Lodge Park</a>. Hugo had given Charlotte on the morning of the wedding about 25 beautifully bound <a href="http://www.penguinclassics.co.uk/">Penguin Classics</a>. (If you''ve not seen these, you need to) The covers are stunning. Each book held a precious message from Hugo. So, so sweet!</div>\n<div>With a mighty Cobra to drive his beauty to the reception Hugo revved that engine big time. It really was like watching a child with his brand new toy. Classic, yet full of vigour. A seriously noisy car at that!</div>\n<div>We feel very honoured to have been able to share in this beautiful celebration. It is always so humbling hearing speeches and learning about our clients from the other wedding guests. We thank you for allowing us to be a part of your beautifully stylish, personal and real wedding day. Thank you x o&c</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-symTHwBFWdQ/T8SaSajbESI/AAAAAAAAAIk/nChkGPerDFU/s1600/H%2526Cwww_001