INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (342, 1, '2012-01-05 12:54:00', '2012-01-05 12:54:00', 'A naval wedding, men in uniform and bride in a beautiful <a href="http://www.stephanieallin.net/">Stephanie Allin</a> dress. Yes please, we said! :D<br>Andy and Hannah met and work for the Navy. Andy is a Captain, while Hannah is a highly skilled logistics officer. Both very high up and highly praised in their rankings. <br>They married in a fabulous ceremony, surrounded by colleagues in uniform. It was quite an emotional thing to see. Men and women, who have fought for our country in Afghanistan and other war torn areas of the world, celebrating together the marriage of two of their colleagues.<br>Andy wore his amazingly smart uniform, along with medals from his recent tour to Afghanistan. Hannah wore on of our favourite dresses of 2011. A beautiful <a href="http://www.stephanieallin.net/">Stephanie Allin</a> dress, with some equally gorgeous <a href="http://rachelsimpsonshoes.co.uk/">Rachel Simpson shoes</a>. It suited her perfectly. Even to the point that during the speeches Andy asked Hannah to stand on a chair, where upon he raised a toast to "the dress!"<br>Their reception was held at <a href="http://www.slebech.co.uk/">Slebech Park</a> and gave us some beautiful opportunities for photographs, with its chapel ruins in the grounds and the estuary than runs alongside the venue, we were spoilt for choice.<br>The beautiful details at the wedding reception, with an array of beautiful bunting, gingham tablecloths, individual soaps and ribbon made for stunning and individual features in the marquee.<br>A truly lovely day and a chance to really celebrate the skills and talents of two people who serve our country and have have found love through the hard work they do.<br>Thank you Andy and Hannah for allowing us to share in and capture your beautiful wedding celebration x o&c<br><br><a href="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7164/6640735567_f1a0cfff86_b.jpg"><img src="http://farm8.s