INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (346, 1, '2011-11-10 14:08:00', '2011-11-10 14:08:00', 'One of our sunniest weddings this "summer". Pat and Abi were married in West Wales surrounded by family, friends and plenty of beautiful floral and diamant detailing.<br>Abi is slightly obsessed with all things pretty and sparkly and had made huge steps to make sure that these things were incorporated in to her special day. Take a look at these amazing shoes. Abi hand decorated them with hundreds of diamant gems. They really were something else. Abi is actually keen to do this more often. We look forward to seeing her talent go from strength to strength!<br>The flowers at the wedding were all styled by Abi''s very talented sister and looked amazing. large hanging balls of blue hydrangeas and bright pink rose bouquets. This girl knows what to do with flowers! (available for hire, so please contact us if you are interested)<br>Pat, a farmer by trade, not so bothered by sparkle, spent the morning in the pub. Calming his nerves with one or five zambuccas and sharing this momentous occasion with his friends and ... the vicar! <br>Living in Pembrokeshire we do have many beautiful beaches for couple shots and we gave a little "whoo-hoo!" when Pat and Abi said they would love to go to Freshwater West. We cant argue with anyone wanting to go there, it is exceptionally beautiful.<br>A reception back at Abi''s parents house allowed for a relaxed, chilled and truly fun atmosphere. We even got involved and "down with the kids" on the bouncy castle and bucking sheep. See if you can spot the sneaky shots of us getting in the with guests and making the most of our super job. Tee hee! ;P<br>Thanks Pat and Abi for choosing us to share in your fun-filled day and choosing such a scorcher of a day to tie the knot! :D x x<br><br><a href="http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6056/6326089974_4d3a21609a_b.jpg"><img src="http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6056/6326089974_4d3a21609a_b.jpg" border="0" alt=""></a>