INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (348, 1, '2011-09-08 14:12:00', '2011-09-08 14:12:00', 'These guys are just truly beautiful. No other words for it. We had not met Va and Joy before they stepped out of their car to meet their friends and family on their wedding day. They greeted us with such beaming smiles and excited emotion, we knew we were in for a special time.<br>Va and Joy had had a civil ceremony before making their way to <a href="http://www.glansevin.com/">Plas Glansevin</a> for their wedding ceremony and reception. These guys got married under an oak tree. It was beautiful! The welsh rain held off and the ceremony was full of emotion and precious moments. Its so special what we as photographers get to witness and capture and this ceremony reminded us of just that. Two people declaring their love under an oak tree, making marriage vows and celebrating with their friends and family. What could be better!<br>Their special day was styled by <a href="http://www.savoirweddings.com/">Savoir Weddings</a>. We found this out just the day before the wedding and were anticipating big things. We were far from disappointed. Jam jars of hand-picked flowers, ribbons and paper lanterns hanging in the tree, delicate colours and simple features that created such a gentle and warm atmosphere, both inside and outside.<br>Va and Joy were some of the most warm and enthusiastic people we have the pleasure to photograph, but what was even more obvious was the deep love they shared with each other. It just oozed from them! <br>We did not stay for the evening celebrations, but know that their evening included a beautifully prepared meal, dancing from a friend and some serious grooving into the small hours.<br>We want to thank you both for your encouragement, excitement and genuine warmth and loveliness on your wedding day. You made us feel at ease and we loved every second of your day. Happy happy marriage to you both Va and Joy x o&c<br><br><a href="http://farm7.static.flickr.co