INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (133, 1, '2013-01-09 10:56:00', '2013-01-09 10:56:00', '<div></div>\n<div>With some many wedding from 2012 yet to blog its really fun being able to look through and share our work and memories with you. Each wedding being so different, being so personal and each a different experience for us as photographers.</div>\n<div>Jon and Jane have been childhood sweethearts and always done life together. When it finally came to their big day, which they had been planning for a very long time, the thought of being apart from each other was hard, although they still wanted the magic of seeing each other for the first time as Jane walked down the aisle. Jon and Jane opted for a "first meet". They didn''t want to actually see each other, but needed the reassurance that they were there. A moment jam packed full of emotion and excitement. In fact, this seemed to be the flavour of the day. Full of beautifully created stationary, design and detailed beauty, Jane created her dream wedding, a true labour of love and skill. When we saw the tent for the first time it truly took our breathe away. They hired a <a href="http://www.wildrosetents.co.uk/">Wild Rose Tent</a>, filling it with floral beauties, colours tins, vintage, mismatched crockery. These tents are something else, seriously!</div>\n<div>With a huge shoe love Jane had three, yes three items of footwear! Two pairs of shoes from <a href="http://www.kurtgeiger.com/">Kurt Geiger</a> and a pair of <a href="http://www.joules.com/">Joules </a>wellies for our trip to the fields for the couple shots. Her dress was a beautiful <a href="http://www.jennypackham.com/">Jenny Packham</a> from the lovely <a href="http://www.whitebride.net/">WhiteBride </a>boutique.</div>\n<div>It was a true honour to share in your wedding day Jon and Jane. Thank you for letting us celebrate with you and for the food too... truly delicious! x o&c</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-XnYqE_lwcfI/UO