INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (361, 1, '2012-11-21 11:05:00', '2012-11-21 11:05:00', '<div></div>One thing about love that is just ace is that love works across cultures. Owen and Myself are a Welsh-Brummie combination and it works! Jacob and Georgie live out in The States, where they met and studied. Jacob is American/<span><span data-vq="/search?hl=en&safe=off&client=firefox-a&hs=NM9&rls=org.mozilla:en-US:official&q=%22costa+rica%22+%22currency%22+%22costa+rican+col%C3%B3n%22&stick=H4sIAAAAAAAAAGOovnz8BQMDAx8HsxKHfq6-gWGBRbEDY72Vs--Uu46_tF-tvGNm-LN5G0tjHQAZ0hR5KwAAAA">Costa Rican</span></span> while Georgie is from Wales. Another super combination! <br>Jacob and Georgie decided to have their wedding in Pembrokeshire, bringing with them family from across the US. For some of them it was their first ever time out of their home town, so was a very special trip. <br>There was so much happiness and jovial celebration. The "The Star Spangled Banner" and "Hen Wlad Fy Nhadau" were both sang with great gusto and the American visitors were treated to a beautiful Welsh day, blue sky and warmth. Obviously a true typical British experience ? :P<br>Oh, and they had, by far the cutest bridesmaid we have ever had the pleasure of meeting. She does feature rather a lot in this post, but Im sure you can see why! <br>Thank you Jacob and Georgie for allowing us to join in the with your celebration x o&c <br><br><div><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-XAS-84VuN-0/UKZL-MuKkqI/AAAAAAAABks/vDqdmZJfb5c/s1600/Jacob+and+Georgie-0011.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-XAS-84VuN-0/UKZL-MuKkqI/AAAAAAAABks/vDqdmZJfb5c/s1600/Jacob+and+Georgie-0011.jpg"></a></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-0feLd0lsR_c/UKZL7DaxgqI/AAAAAAAABkc/WNVLqpXZKbY/s1600/Jacob+and+Georgie-0003.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-0feLd0lsR_c/UKZL7DaxgqI/AAAAAAAABkc/WNVLqpXZKbY/s1600/Jacob+and+Georgie-000