INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (362, 1, '2012-11-15 12:04:00', '2012-11-15 12:04:00', '<div>Its always lovely when we get the chance to get excited about a wedding day. When we booked Chris and Teresa they had just over a year to go to their big day. They had plenty of ideas and plans in place, but as the year drew on, more and more ideas were coming out of the woodwork. We knew we''d have a fabulous time with this pair.</div>\n<div>Chris and Teresa had a double ceremony wedding at <a href="http://www.slebech.co.uk/">Slebech Park </a>in Pembrokeshire. They began their day with their marriage ceremony and then headed on over to a beautiful castle ruins for their wedding blessing. With old walled vegetable gardens and tall tree wooded areas the venue opened up such beautiful backdrops for photos. We were pretty much in our element!</div>\n<div>We always say to our couples we try to capture aspects of the day that make their day "their day".</div>\n<div>Beautiful details from start to finish made Chris and Teresa''s day, very much their own. From the sweet and thoughtful gifts they gave each before their ceremony, sock monkeys for the children, home-made jams for guests and the handmade photo booth for guests. It was obvious every ounce of thought and love had been put in to make sure that the day they had dreamt of was turned into a reality.</div>\n<div>Thank you to you both for allowing us to be part of such a fun, beautiful and personal day x x o&c</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-P-xaSuaULFc/UKTM2vHc8yI/AAAAAAAABZE/lzoePWddQIc/s1600/Chris+and+Teresa-0001.jpg"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-P-xaSuaULFc/UKTM2vHc8yI/AAAAAAAABZE/lzoePWddQIc/s1600/Chris+and+Teresa-0001.jpg"></a></div>\n<div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-6SFJ7IPwgOo/UKTM4sDGtaI/AAAAAAAABZM/NKh_DJ_6xlY/s1600/Chris+and+Teresa-0006.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-6SFJ7IPwgOo/UKTM4sDGtaI/AAAAAAAABZM/NKh_DJ_6xlY/s1600