INSERT INTO `wp_photo_posts` VALUES (667, 1, '2012-06-10 12:04:00', '2012-06-10 12:04:00', '<div></div><div></div>Its not every day you have the pleasure of photographing the wedding of a friend. Ive known Hayley for a good few years now and remember clearly when she told me she''d met this lovely Scottish fella!<br>Of course, I was exctied and even more so when they asked if we would be their photographers.<br>I knew that Hayley would go for a few quirky bits and pieces in her wedding day and we were far from disappointed. I remember getting tweets about her shoes, lace pop socks and the bridesmaids dresses( from <a href="http://www.bravissimo.com/pepperberry/">Bravissimo</a>) and wellies and their stunning hand stitched brooches & rings made by super talented <a href="http://www.etsy.com/shop/bettythread">Betty Thread. </a><br><div><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-RWYjJyI5G4A/T9SL6ooHiSI/AAAAAAAAAX8/ctiHNbHI5Y8/s1600/Lucy+Ledger_002.jpg" imageanchor="1"><br></a></div>Paul and Hayley were married in a small parish church in the beautiful Suffolk village of Copdock. Afterwards we hopped over a stile for the couple shots after stumbling over a lovely barn. (Oh man, we could have stayed there all day) These guys were so much fun and there were treasures to be had in every nook and cranny!<br>I think the photos pretty much speak for themselves. Two gorgeous people, love, and a wedding day.<br>Thanks so much for allowing us to share in your day Paul and Hayley and thanks again to Kat of Rock and Roll Bride for kindly<span> </span><a href="http://www.rocknrollbride.com/2012/02/a-colourful-barn-wedding-paul-hayley/"><span>sharing this wedding on her blog too</span>.</a> x x o&c<br><br><div><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-MPyUfbqgF0I/T9HTVYot5yI/AAAAAAAAAQA/Bh0k5BpXhFU/s1600/H%2526Cwww_010.jpg"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-MPyUfbqgF0I/T9HTVYot5yI/AAAAAAAAAQA/Bh0k5BpXhFU/s1600/H%2526Cwww_010.jpg"></a></div><div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-Az0_b